Why Apache Camel?
1. Camel is a java based framework designed to easily embed within web or standalone java application.
   Camel is just a set of libraries you can put it in your web-based java application. Suppose we are writing some sort of MVC application or rest based application doesn't matter, what web
application we are writing you can literally embed this.
   We can have a standalone java application or spring boot application which is some sort of ETL which just taking data, transforming data and sending downstream you can use it, rather than writing a lot of boilerplate code.

2. It uses Java DSL(Domain Specific Language) or XML to build routes 
       The team come up with some sort of simple syntax which everybody can understand and then they can start building their routes and end points so they come up with Java DSL, same thing works in xml also

3. Pojo based model
      Camel works with pojo, you create a bean, you put it into apache camel's exchange,you store that information in camel, you just pass it on to your route, you pull it again to manipulate the data, send it again on the route it just works. We don't need to worry about how camel is storing it internally 

4. simple and consistent format 
       The dsl or xml provides this consistent formatwhen you are building your routes. You always get data from something, then you are processing and then you're sending to a destination.
It doesn't matter what technology we are using it could be a database or file system or web or any messaging system, we want to read from this place, we want to do the processing and send it to this destination 

5.  Apache camel has got support for all the technologies which are available in the enterprise world, any database like rdbms,nosql, messaging system like ibm mq, rabbitmq, kafka or file systems or any protocol, it has a component to  support it
    Component means you just give the connection details such as username password for databases or messaging it takes care of underlying protocols, we don't need to really worry about how we are going to connect to that database or messaging system you just give the credentials, camel will take over it knows exactly how to talk to that technology or that protocol and it just manages it

6. Support for over 50 data formats - Data formats like  json or xm, also we have standard formats 
in the financial sector, in the telecom sector, in the healthcare etc

7. Pluggable architecture - Apache camel has comes with 150 components,over 50 formats, but there is always a possibility that the thing which you are trying to do in your organization or in your project it might not have a support. So you can build your own component or data format and you can just plug it

8. Test kit - what's the point of creating a market leading framework or application if it cannot be tested easily by the  system which is going to consume that library
   Apache camel has solved that problem, it comes up with camel test framework ,you can mock your routes, you can try to integrate with in-memory, you can test the whole thing. Not only you
can do unit testing, you can do some sort of you know integration testing using this framework

