- Escaping Characters with RAW values in URI
      Consider we want our files to be renamed and the name of the new file should start with
& sign, for example &file.txt so to rename our files after they are moved we use filename end point option, but as you can see if we just & it breaks our URI because any string after & is
treated like a separate option

.toD("file:src/main/resources/files/output/${body}?fileName=&file.txt")

So to escape this & symbol we should use RAW construction, any symbols inside its brackets do not count toward URL validation

   public void configure() {
    	from("file:src/main/resources/files?noop={{my.camel.property.noop}}&filter=#my-file-filter")
                .log("Message: ${body}, Headers: ${headers}")
                .toD("file:src/main/resources/files/output/${body}?fileName=RAW(&file.txt)");;
    }

