Implementing Content-Based Routing
       Imagine our message has some kind of content, for example header and based on the value of
that content we want to send our message to different destinations. In our example, we have this request type header and based on its value, we want to send it in different queues, if request type equal statement we want to send it to statement.queue, if request type is payment details we want to send it to paymentdetails.queue and in the case that we can't identify our request type we will send it to unrecognized.queue, to do such kind of content-based routing we use Choice DSL
element.  After choice(), we can declare one or more when() DSL element to specify our conditions which takes Predicate as argument


 public void configure() {
        from("jms:input.queue")
                .log("Body: ${body}, Headers: ${headers}")
                .choice()
                .when(exchange -> {
                    //we know exchange is a container for message, so to get message header first
					//we use exchange.getMessage.getHeader
                    Object requestType = exchange.getMessage().getHeader("requestType");
                    if (requestType != null) {
                        return "statement".equals(requestType);
                    }
                    return false;
                })
                    .to("jms:statement.queue") //send msg to statement.queue
                .when(simple("${header.requestType} == 'paymentDetails'")) //even we can use 															//simple language to fetch the header details 
                    .to("jms:request.details.queue")
                .otherwise()
                    .to("jms:unrecognised.queue")
                .end()  //we need to close our choice with end() DSL element
                .log("Processing ended.");  //log the info 
    }

