5.  Run our appl and we will see that nothing changes because again this is basically a default
configuration we don't need to write it, it is enabled in any camel route

6. Now we see what we can configure with our defaultErrorHandler and it has its own DSL like like maximumRedeliveries and reDeliveryDelay

from("timer:ticker?period=1s")
         .errorHandler(defaultErrorHandler().maximumRedeliveries(3).redeliveryDelay(500))
         .setBody(simple("Hello World"))    
         .process(exchange -> {
             throw new RuntimeException("Test exception");
         })
         .log("Ended route with body: ${body}");

This means that our message will be retried three times with a delay of 500 milliseconds, in our case this is pointless because we know that we are getting the exception, but in many other cases this might make sense, because for example if we're getting an HTTP timeout then trying
again might be a valid option, it is also worth that when we retry our message it is retried from the point of failure. So when we retry our message three times in this example, we're
actually retrying this process step three times but we don't setBody three times, this might be important in the case we do some processing before we encounter an error 

