7. Testing Camel Routes with Spring Boot
           We can unit test our camel routes with regular spring boot test annotation. we can inject our context using our regular mockito annotations to mock our spring beans, but we want to
know two annotations,
  1. @EndpointInject allows you to inject mock endpoints, you don't need to get them from camel
context, you're just specify mock endpoint name and you will get it
    @EndpointInject("mock:example-route-test")
    private MockEndpoint mock;

  2. @Produce annotation injects a ProducerTemplate configured to write messages to this exact end point that we've specified here
    @Produce(directTestEndpoint)
