1. Create SpringBootRESTCamel with  web, spring data jpa, h2,validation, lombok, swagger dependency

When you create a Spring Boot app with spring-boot-starter-web, Spring Boot auto-configures an embedded HTTP server (Tomcat by default, but can also be Jetty or Undertow). Apache Camel is just a routing engine — it doesn’t run an HTTP server by itself.
It relies on components to consume/produce messages.

For HTTP, Camel provides multiple components:
camel-servlet → runs on top of a Servlet container (like Tomcat).
camel-platform-http → integrates with Spring Boot’s HTTP server via spring-boot-starter-web.
camel-undertow → runs its own Undertow server if you prefer.

👉 When you use Spring Boot + camel-platform-http, Camel registers handlers/endpoints on the existing Spring Boot server.

