How to use Aggregator EIP using Spring and Apache Camel?
      Sometimes, multiple messages belong together (e.g., order items that form one invoice).
Instead of processing them individually, you want to aggregate them into one combined exchange.
Camel provides the Aggregator EIP using .aggregate() DSL.
       When u r implementing aggregator design patterns there are few must have configurations
1. Correlation identifier - It is an expression that determines which incoming messages belong together, because we have bunch of messages coming and we like to have some sort of condition and we can try to put those messages which are matching ur criteria and then create one final out message

2. Completion condition - Along with combining the message we also like to have some condition, so if these conditions are matched then ur message is completed and ready to send out

3. Aggregation strategy - specifies how to combine the messages into a single message 

Real world example
     As a customer we want to buy a car, so we go to some price comparing website and fills details about the car and it will be submitted to the server. Now server will validating and once everything is correct, this server has to talk to various insurance brokers, consider we have bunch of insurance brokers 
    Now the server needs to submit the form to these insurance brokers and those insurance companies have to provide the price info as response. Now the server will aggregate all these prices and verify whether it meets the customer criteria or not and return the final response to the customer 
    You can write ur own logic to aggregate and build this complex logic with lot of coding, instead we have Enterprise Integration pattern to solve these realworld problems
    In camel, we will write a camel route which take request from customer and send to bunch of insurance brokers and once the price has come back, it automatically knows how to aggregate it and send the response back 

Example
   We have string which is sending some message with aggregation id or correlation id, so based on that id we can build logic (ie) whenever we see same id 3 times then we like to join the messages 

1. Create SpringBootAggregator project with camel, web dependency

2. Create route
       In real world we will be connecting with messaging queue or database and messages will be coming through and we will be reading it. 
      In our case we are using timer component to create bunch of messages, this timer component will initiate an event and whenever this event occurs we put a new message in body using process() and log the event

@Component
public class AggregatorRoute extends RouteBuilder {

	@Override
	public void configure() throws Exception {
		from("timer:insurance?period=200")
        .process(exchange -> {
         Message message = exchange.getMessage();
         message.setBody(new Date());
         })
        .log(LoggingLevel.ERROR, "${body}");
	}

}

