Now we have written a route which streams the messages. Now we want to aggregate the message when some ID is matching, here we wont have any id in case if it is coming from some source that process will send some ID. Since we are creating stream over here, one of the rule of aggregation strategy is that every header message needs to contain some correlation id or unique id 
    Now we set the header with unique identifier called correlationId and hardcoded the value as 1 (ie) every stream message that comes will have an id as 1 and print the correlationId

@Component
public class AggregatorRoute extends RouteBuilder {
	
	final String CORRELATION_ID = "correlationId";

	@Override
	public void configure() throws Exception {
		from("timer:insurance?period=200")
		.process(exchange -> {
	         Message message = exchange.getMessage();
	         message.setHeader(CORRELATION_ID, 1);
	         message.setBody(new Date());
	         })
		.log(LoggingLevel.ERROR, "${header." + CORRELATION_ID + "} ${body}");
	}

}

