- Next we implement aggregation using aggregate() DSL element, first thing we have to pass is what is the correlationid based on which we can aggregate the data, second thing we have to pass a class which implements AggregationStrategy interface 

@Override
	public void configure() throws Exception {
		from("timer:insurance?period=200")
		.process(exchange -> {
	         Message message = exchange.getMessage();
	         message.setHeader(CORRELATION_ID, 1);
	         message.setBody(new Date());
	         })
		.aggregate(header(CORRELATION_ID), new MyAggregationStrategy())
		.log(LoggingLevel.ERROR, "${header." + CORRELATION_ID + "} ${body}");
	}

- Create MyAggregationStrategy class which implements AggregationStrategy and override aggregate() which takes oldExchange and newExchange
     So everytime when stream comes to camel route, it automatically going to filter based on id 


public class MyAggregationStrategy implements org.apache.camel.AggregationStrategy {
    @Override
    public Exchange aggregate(Exchange oldExchange, Exchange newExchange) {

//For firsttime call to this method we dont have any old value so it returns new value. So camel stores in memory so nexttime camels see same correlationid, it will call aggregate() once again and return newExchange as oldvalue. So camel will stores all this info and it is aware of oldExchange, newExchange 
        if (Objects.isNull(oldExchange)) {
            return newExchange;
        }

        //Extract msg from oldExchange
        String oldBody = oldExchange.getIn().getBody(String.class);
        //Extract msg from newExchange
        String newBody = newExchange.getIn().getBody(String.class);

//Now we can do any processing on the message we extracted from body, this is called as aggregation, now we concatenate oldBody and newBody into separate variable aggBody 
        String aggBody = oldBody + "->" + newBody;

//Next we need to set this message in our exchange, so nexttime when camel sees same identifier it can give oldobject as well as newobject
        oldExchange.getIn().setBody(aggBody);

        return oldExchange;
    }
}

- We have told camel to aggregate based on correlationid and strategy class which has business logic, now we have to say at what point aggregation should be finish using completionSize(), because we are collecting the messages but we should finish at times 

@Override
	public void configure() throws Exception {
		from("timer:insurance?period=200")
		.process(exchange -> {
	         Message message = exchange.getMessage();
	         message.setHeader(CORRELATION_ID, 1);
	         message.setBody(new Date());
	         })
		.aggregate(header(CORRELATION_ID), new MyAggregationStrategy())
		.completionSize(3)
		.log(LoggingLevel.ERROR, "${header." + CORRELATION_ID + "} ${body}");
	}

So here whenever it has joined 3 messages then it should finish the aggregation and once finished we log to see the completion message. So log will be executed only if all 3 aggregations are completed 
   So when route started we started consuming some messages, then we put some aggregation logic, then we told the criteria on what point it should finishing and log will be called only if that completion is matched 

