Circuit Breaker Design Pattern using Apache Camel
        Circuit breaker basically encapsulates the operation and then it monitors it for
failures, it has three stages.
1. closed means when everything is operating successfully, we do not have any failure in your software
2. open - we may make a call to external service or some resource, you detected a failure then application will basically stop sending the load to that resource or API okay and which means now
circuit breaker has been opened 
3. half open  means after a short period in the open State, an operation is attempted to see whether it can complete successfully, so basically we are just trying to check the resource
which was failing earlier has it come back or not, if the answer comes no then we go back to this open State one more time, if answer comes yes (ie) service has recovered and we see successful
responses then we basically reset our breaker and then we go to this closed State 

Usecase
     We are giving a call to a webservice, when call to service takes more than 500ms and 99% of
the requests fail then hold subsequent request for five seconds and return some sort of static response  after that we retry 

1. Create SpringbootCamelCircuitBreaker project with camel, web, camel circuit breaker and camel http server dependency 

